Running the Server
Method 1: Direct execution (recommended for development)
	# Development mode with auto-reload
	python epics_fastapi_gateway.py --dev

	# Production mode
	python epics_fastapi_gateway.py
Method 2: Using uvicorn command
	# Development mode
	uvicorn epics_fastapi_gateway:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

	# Production mode (single worker)
	uvicorn epics_fastapi_gateway:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

	# Production mode (multiple workers)
	uvicorn epics_fastapi_gateway:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4


Method 3: Using gunicorn (best for production)
	gunicorn epics_fastapi_gateway:app \
    		--workers 4 \
    		--worker-class uvicorn.workers.UvicornWorker \
    		--bind 0.0.0.0:8000 \
    		--access-logfile - \
    		--error-logfile -

1. Create the React + Vite Project Run one of the following commands in your terminal:bash

# Latest version (recommended)
npm create vite@latest

# Or specify a version
npm create vite@latest my-project -- --template react

Alternatively, you can do it in one command:bash

npm create vite@latest my-project -- --template react-ts

2. Navigate to the Project Directorybash

cd my-project

3. Install Dependenciesbash

npm install

4. Start the Development Serverbash

npm run dev

